suppressedVulnerability.name: CVE-2022-1471
suppressedVulnerability.description: SnakeYaml's Constructor() class does not restrict types which can be instantiated during deserialization. Deserializing yaml content provided by an attacker can lead to remote code execution. We recommend using SnakeYaml's SafeConsturctor when parsing untrusted content to restrict deserialization.
suppressedVulnerability.notes: CVE relates to constructor which is not used by Jackson
